RULES
- The plan window is a hard constraint: start and end dates are fixed — do not schedule any session before the start date or after the end date
- Only schedule sessions on days with available hours
- Available hours per day are the MAXIMUM — NOT a target. A session SHOULD be shorter than max when the target TSS can be reached in less time, when the athlete is in a recovery/taper phase, or when the session type is naturally short (VO2max, threshold). Using max hours every day is a common mistake — shorter is often better.
- Each session's tss_target must be physically achievable given its duration and session_type. Reference: endurance (Z2) ~55–75 TSS/hour; threshold ~85–100 TSS/hour; VO2max intervals in Z2 base ~70–100 TSS/hour; recovery (Z1) ~20–35 TSS/hour. A 3h endurance ride cannot be 115 TSS.
- Week-level tss_target must equal the sum of that week's session tss_targets (±5%).
- No workout step detail: titles and types only (steps are generated separately per session)

